ory of European fascism. Deeply researched and beautifully written, Ross Cole provides us with a biography of a people who exist only as a symptom of the modern imagination, and the archaeology of a landscape directing flows of global populism to this day.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aFolk MusicxPolitical aspectsxHistoryy19th century. 0aFolk MusicxPolitical aspectsxHistoryy20th century. 0aFolk musicxPolitical aspectsxHistoryy19th century. 0aFolk musicxPolitical aspectsxHistoryy20th century. 0aFolk songsxPolitical aspectsxHistoryy19th century. 0aFolk songsxPolitical aspectsxHistoryy20th century. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Folk & Traditional.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069041508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520383753zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520383753423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520383753/original  a978-3-11-069041-5  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  